Plenoptic cameras, also known as light field cameras, have gained significant traction in various industries due to their ability to capture depth information along with images. The market for plenoptic cameras is segmented based on product type, application, and distribution channel. In terms of product type, there are standard plenoptic cameras and light field cameras. The standard plenoptic camera captures more information about the intensity of light, while the light field camera captures information about the direction of the light rays in addition to intensity. In terms of application, plenoptic cameras find applications in healthcare for medical imaging, automotive for advanced driver-assistance systems, consumer electronics for virtual reality applications, robotics for 3D mapping, and security and surveillance for enhanced monitoring capabilities. In terms of distribution channel, plenoptic cameras are sold both online and offline, with online channels providing convenience and a wider reach, while offline channels offer a personalized shopping experience.

